issue.body:
### Problem

`prefers-color-scheme` [can be used](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/@media/prefers-color-scheme) to modify styling of elements depending on light/dark color themes. However using that currently tracks the OS color scheme and ignores the light/dark setting in Streamlit. This leads to mismatches when a user (or developer) explicitly selects light/dark mode instead of using the "Use system setting" option.

Here is an example of the mismatch, using the example from the linked docs:

[![Open in Streamlit Cloud](https://static.streamlit.io/badges/streamlit_badge_black_white.svg)](https://issues.streamlitapp.com/?issue=gh-6456)

```python
import streamlit as st


st.write(
    """<style>
.theme-a {
  background: #dca;
  color: #731;
}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .theme-a.adaptive {
    background: #753;
    color: #dcb;
    outline: 5px dashed #000;
  }
}
.theme-b {
  background: #447;
  color: #bbd;
}
@media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
  .theme-b.adaptive {
    background: #bcd;
    color: #334;
    outline: 5px dotted #000;
  }
}
</style>
<div class="box theme-a">Theme A (initial)</div>
<div class="box theme-a adaptive">Theme A (changed if dark preferred)</div>
<br />
<div class="box theme-b">Theme B (initial)</div>
<div class="box theme-b adaptive">Theme B (changed if light preferred)</div>
""",
    unsafe_allow_html=True,
)
```

#### System theme light, app theme light (or "Use system setting"):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7876996/230677451-bcc02cab-fe9b-4635-b384-2bc849bb2508.png)
#### System theme light, app theme dark (mismatch):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7876996/230677776-7c39b683-05ab-43ed-a679-6a83b0dfaca1.png)
#### System theme dark, app theme dark (or "Use system setting"):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7876996/230677703-e4f04da6-9ee1-46cd-a343-13fb7b5db80e.png)
#### System theme dark, app theme light (mismatch):
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7876996/230677487-99d49ead-296c-42ec-8fb5-9876022666af.png)


### Solution

**Workarounds:** #3990 or #5009 would help work around it since it would let the developer adjust the styling programmatically.

**Preferred solution:** Somehow propagating the streamlit theme choice so `prefers-color-scheme` works as expected.

### Additional context

In my case I embed an SVG that has its own styling, but it can use `prefers-color-scheme` in its `style` property to determine whether the background is dark or white and color its elements accordingly. Since the SVG that has a transparent background, elements that I draw on it will not be visible if the system theme doesn't match the app theme.

Right now I set `base = "light"` in the streamlit config and configure my SVG styling accordingly, but users can still change it through the settings menu and that breaks visibility.

